BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Early Bird Hike with Ben Fleet
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T000000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T000000
UID:251224VkyzcF54c0q9_p31gAE7Zw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/_3ZMEogspUG1pbTVbWQUQw.large.png
DESCRIPTION:This hike was rescheduled to March 22\, 9-11am\, due to high w
 inds.\\*\\*\\* This Early Bird Hike is perfect for those looking to get ou
 tside and enjoy the serenity of the natural world at dawn. Ben will help y
 ou identify the birds calling and singing in the cool morning air\, includ
 ing a variety of songbirds\, waterfowl\, and woodpeckers as they prepare f
 or spring. With the spring migration just beginning\, March is a fantastic
  time to catch sight of some returning species like Robins\, Red-winged Bl
 ackbirds\, Cedar Waxwings\, and perhaps even the first of the warblers. Th
 e preserve's mix of wetlands\, woodlands\, and meadows provides the perfec
 t habitat for a variety of bird species. Along the way\, we'll discuss the
  early behaviors of these birds-what they're feeding on\, where they're mi
