BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Saving the Hoosier: The Concert
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T140000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T160000
UID:260309gfMhOqFJhESzcv_Uc-Ew9A
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/rpsBfvZkY0u2duLWxxPHsw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:​Join us for SAVING THE HOOSIER: THE CONCERT and connect wit
 h people who care about the future of OUR Hoosier National Forest while yo
 u enjoy live music up close. The live concert will feature Hoosier musicia
 ns Sarah Flint and Jeff Shew\, and is a fundraiser to help complete the ne
 w documentary film “Saving the Hoosier: The Fight for America’s Forest
 s”. You will get to see a sneak peek of scenes from the film and meet na
 rrator Hud Mellencamp! There will also be a brief talkback with cast membe
 rs following the sneak peek.\n\nWhile there\, enjoy some food and the oppo
 rtunity to bid on locally-made and donated auction items. The film is bein
 g produced by Bloomington-based Women with Guts Productions. There will al
 so be a brief talkback with members of the cast following the screening.\n
 \nWith Artists for Climate Awareness as fiscal sponsor for the film\, dona
 tions are tax-deductible. Tickets for the concert are $30\, and include be
 verages and pizza\, generously donated by Pizza X. \\(please note: $20 of 
 the ticket price is tax-deductible\; $10 allocated for food/ beverages is 
 not\\) Audience members will be invited to participate in a sing-along of 
 the Indiana state song\, "On the Banks of the Wabash"' that will be used i
 n the film.\n\n"Saving the Hoosier" follows environmental activists who\, 
 through grassroots education and lawsuits\, have successfully protected th
 e Hoosier National Forest from the US Forest Service’s plans for commerc
 ial logging and prescribed burns to benefit timber sales.\n\nFor tickets\,
  please visit: https://savingthehoosier.eventbrite.com/\n\nThanks in advan
 ce for your support as we are \\#SavingTheHoosier!!!
