BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:2026 State of the City
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260331T180000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260331T213000
UID:260209hlhmIovafkaf5nYoUJxiMw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/BPE3dYt5KkihhoGzhuNl5g.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Mayor Kerry Thomson will take the stage for Bloomington’s 2
 026 State of the City\, an evening dedicated to where we’ve been\, where
  we’re headed\, and how we move forward together.\n\nThis free\, public 
 event invites residents\, businesses\, and community partners to gather do
 wntown for a shared look at Bloomington’s progress and priorities. Doors
  open at 5:30 p.m.\, with the program beginning at 6 p.m.\, followed by a 
 reception to connect with neighbors and city leadership.\n\nThis year’s 
 State of the City will spotlight the big-picture work shaping Bloomington 
 right now—from housing and public safety to economic vitality\, infrastr
 ucture\, transparency\, and long-term financial stewardship. Mayor Thomson
  will reflect on milestones from the past year and outline the path ahead 
 for a city that continues to serve with intention\, creativity\, and care.
 \n\nCan’t attend in person? The event will be livestreamed and available
  for later viewing through Community Access Television Services \\(CATS\\)
  on local cable and at catstv.net.\n\nWe hope you’ll join us.
LOCATION:Buskirk Chumley Theater
URL:https://buskirkchumley.org/events/2026-state-of-the-city-march-31-2026
 /
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Bloomington
END:VEVENT
