BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:InterACTION: Harmony School Art Show
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260403T170000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260403T200000
UID:260211Smw7hON0D0-tRdmf1raVcQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/SPWsmqNrpU6Czop9Ezzegw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:March is Art Month at Harmony School and students spend the wh
 ole month collaborating with local artists to create pieces for our upcomi
 ng art show: InterACTION! Art Month introduces students to unconventional 
 mediums and gives them the chance to experience and create art in motion!\
 n\nInterACTION revolves around two central themes: interaction and movemen
 t. With these in mind\, Bloomington artists like Joel Washington and Sarah
  Wolfe will be working closely with Harmony students to help them put toge
 ther unique displays that engage both their creativity and viewers.\n\nSho
 w entry is FREE and will be a part of the First Friday Gallery Walk! Appet
 izers and refreshments will be served throughout the event. \n\nWe hope t
 o see you there on Friday\, April 3rd at 5:00 PM - 8:00 PM!\n\nSelect work
 s will be displayed in Fountain Square Mall through May.\n\nGet all the In
 terACTION updates and news by following us @harmonyschoolbloomington on al
 l social media platforms!
