BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Stavros Halkias: The Dreamboat Tour
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260409T190000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260409T210000
UID:251028ZVP1P1-LDkqv7bXe6z8Oww
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/YRlGt14qfUqMuhcz_NYzPQ.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Stavros Halkias is a comedian\, actor\, and writer from Balti
 more\, Maryland\, now based in New York City. He most recently wrote\, pro
 duced\, and starred in the indie comedy Let’s Start a Cult. His latest s
 tand-up special\, Fat Rascal\, is streaming on Netflix\, following his deb
 ut special Live at the Lodge Room\, which hit one million views in its fi
 rst four days and has since surpassed seven million.\n\nOne of the most in
 -demand touring comedians today\, Halkias is currently on The Dreamboat To
 ur. His podcast Stavvy’s World debuted at \\#3 on the iTunes Comedy Cha
 rts\, amassing hundreds of thousands of subscribers in its first year. He 
 will soon appear in Yorgos Lanthimos’ Bugonia\, premiering at the Venic
 e Film Festival\, and in A24’s Tony\, a film about Anthony Bourdain. He 
 also stars in the Netflix comedy series Tires\, bringing his quick wit an
 d offbeat charm to television audiences.\n\nA founding member and former c
 o-host of the hit podcast Cum Town \\(2016–2022\\)\, Halkias has also 
 been featured in Steven Soderbergh’s sci-fi series Command Z. Outside of
  comedy\, he made his runway debut at KidSuper’s Paris Fashion Week show
  in 2023\, earning Vogue’s nod as “the plus-est of plus-size models.
 ” His ultimate dream? Get just famous enough to buy his mother a nice ho
 me—then retire from show business to open a surf-and-turf restaurant in 
 East Baltimore.
LOCATION:Buskirk Chumley Theater
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#/details/stavros-halkias-the-dreamboat
 -tour/17240007/2026-04-09T19
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Bloomington
END:VEVENT
