BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Asianfest 2026
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260411T190000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260411T210000
UID:260207Brz8hYH6v0ywqgadsbFlPQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/4h6oZZ6TnUilFkEnNoW5fA.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:AsianFest 2026 – Mosaic Traditions: Piecing a Common Ground\
 n\nAsianFest 2026 is a celebration of the shared histories and diverse her
 itages of Asian American and Pacific Islander \\(AAPI\\) communities\, wit
 hin Indiana University and the broader Bloomington community. The event hi
 ghlights the richness and diversity through cultural expression\, storytel
 ling\, and artistic performance. Guided by this year’s theme\, we invite
  all attendees to reflect\, connect\, and find peace on common ground.\n\n
 Taking place on April 11\, 2026 and organized by the Asian Culture Center 
 at Indiana University \\(ACC\\)\, the event brings together AAPI communiti
 es from across Indiana University and the wider Bloomington area.\n\nThe p
 rogram features cultural and informational tabling from 4:00–6:00 PM ins
 ide the Buskirk-Chumley Theater \\(BCT\\) venue\, followed by a staged pro
 gram from 7:00–8:30 PM that includes video screenings and live performan
 ces showcasing AAPI voices and traditions.\n\nThe events and programs with
 in AsianFest 2026 are open to all members of Indiana University and the wi
 der Bloomington community. We welcome everyone regardless of age\, cultura
 l affinity\, background\, or identity.\n\nThis event is FREE! No tickets a
 re needed for entry.
LOCATION:Buskirk Chumley Theater
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#/details/asianfest-2026/18055244/2026-
 04-11T19
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Bloomington
END:VEVENT
