 ortalimages/portalimages/O330VgnfgkWT3M9XENdZeA.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Come see our local Red-eared Slider hunt for fish. This progra
 m is held at the Canyon Inn.  \n\nNature Center is open every day from 10 
 am-5 pm EDT in April-Novemember \n\nUpcoming programs can be seen by visit
 ing on.in.gov/mccormickscreek\n\nOur interpretive programs are designed to
  entertain and enrich folks of all ages. Children under 12 must have an ad
 ult with them at the programs.\n\nRegistration is not required for program
 s \\(unless stated\\). All our programs are free \\(unless otherwise noted
 \\). They are open to the public after paying the park entrance fee \\($7 
 in-state & $12 out-of-state\\).\n\nAll our Interpretive programs are liste
 d in Eastern Daylight Savings Time.\n\n\\*Note that during peak visitation
  times\, entry into our park might be delayed. The drive to the Nature Cen
 ter can take 8 minutes. Please plan accordingly. \\*\n\nIf you need more i
 nformation\, call 812-829-2235 ext. 2
LOCATION:McCormick's Creek State Park
URL:https://events.in.gov/event/turtle-feeding-mccormicks-creek-state-park
