BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:African American Dance Company Spring Concert
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260418T193000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260418T213000
UID:260218zgjtqLASXkCtznM24tsNUQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/FzMV8Mqofk6FKYtCKEUzdw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The legendary African American Dance Company presents its An
 nual Spring Concert on Saturday\, April 18\, 2026\, 7:30 p.m. at Buskirk-C
 humley Theater in Bloomington\, IN.\n\nDirected by Baba Stafford C. Berry 
 Jr.\, the African American Dance Company shares movement traditions from A
 frica\, the diaspora\, and from African American culture. Since its foundi
 ng in 1974\, the African American Dance Company has performed throughout I
 ndiana\, in New York City\, and internationally in China\, Jamaica\, and C
 uba. The company’s repertoire includes African dance styles\, contempora
 ry\, modern\, jazz\, hip-hop\, and various cultural forms.\n\nThe African 
 American Dance Company is a course offered for credit through the Departme
 nt of African American and African Diaspora Studies\, and is one of three 
 performing ensembles managed by African American Arts Institute at Indiana
  University Bloomington.
LOCATION:Buskirk Chumley Theater
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#/details/african-american-dance-compan
 y-spring-concert/18145892/2026-04-18T19
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Bloomington
END:VEVENT
