DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260515T210000
UID:260314CR0jebOrckSWMdbHAZreyg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/A94P2qQ7FEG57DC7QqeebQ.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Constellation Stage and Screen & BCT Present: Mamma Mia! \\(2
 008\\)\n\nCalling all dancing queens and super troupers! Experience the ma
 gic of ABBA’s greatest hits on the big screen in this feel-good movie mu
 sical about a bride-to-be searching for her real father. Based on the Broa
 dway musical of the same name\, Mamma Mia! is a high-energy celebration of
  love\, friendship\, and timeless pop classics.\n\nPre-Show Extravaganza: 
 Be sure to dress in your Mamma Mia best\, because we’re kicking off the 
 screening with a costume contest! Show off your disco- and island-inspired
  looks for the chance to win a fabulous prize. Come early to take photos a
 t our photo booth and grab a themed cocktail from the bar.
LOCATION:Buskirk Chumley Theater
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#/details/mamma-mia-2008/18326768/2026-
 05-15T19
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Bloomington
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Finn: A New Musical- At the PB&J Cafe
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260515T183000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260515T183000
UID:250915uZFWUrlI_EGiY_fAgymRwA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/r64S3_evs0KRGCSVU8SpIQ.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Constellation Stage & Screen presents “Finn: A New Musical- 
 At the PB&J Cafe\,” on stage May 1-17 at the Waldron Auditorium. \n\nFr
 om the creator of Doc McStuffins and Vampirina\, Finn is a heartwarming mu
 sical adventure about a young shark on the brink of growing up. As he prep
 ares to join the fearsome Shark Guard\, Finn can’t shake the feeling tha
 t he’s different from the other sharks. Deep inside\, he discovers a col
 orful fish inside him—a part of himself that longs to sparkle\, sing\, a
 nd dance. As Finn embarks on a journey of self-discovery\, friendship\, an
 d adventure\, he finds the courage to be himself! Fun for all ages!\n\nPB&
 J Cafe: A Dinner Theater for Kids! At the PB&J Cafe\, young theatergoers w
 ill enjoy a meal during the performance and leave with autographs from the
 ir favorite characters. \n\nSee Constellation’s website for more inform
 ation\, including a detailed performance schedule. Learn more and find tic
 kets at https://seeconstellation.org/kids/finn/
LOCATION:Waldron Auditorium
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#/details/finn-a-new-musical-at-the-pb-
 j-cafe/16788679/2026-05-15T18
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Bloomington
END:VEVENT
