 ortalimages/portalimages/r64S3_evs0KRGCSVU8SpIQ.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Constellation Stage & Screen presents “Finn: A New Musical- 
 At the PB&J Cafe\,” on stage May 1-17 at the Waldron Auditorium. \n\nFr
 om the creator of Doc McStuffins and Vampirina\, Finn is a heartwarming mu
 sical adventure about a young shark on the brink of growing up. As he prep
 ares to join the fearsome Shark Guard\, Finn can’t shake the feeling tha
 t he’s different from the other sharks. Deep inside\, he discovers a col
 orful fish inside him—a part of himself that longs to sparkle\, sing\, a
 nd dance. As Finn embarks on a journey of self-discovery\, friendship\, an
 d adventure\, he finds the courage to be himself! Fun for all ages!\n\nPB&
 J Cafe: A Dinner Theater for Kids! At the PB&J Cafe\, young theatergoers w
 ill enjoy a meal during the performance and leave with autographs from the
 ir favorite characters. \n\nSee Constellation’s website for more inform
 ation\, including a detailed performance schedule. Learn more and find tic
 kets at https://seeconstellation.org/kids/finn/
LOCATION:Waldron Auditorium
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#/details/finn-a-new-musical-at-the-pb-
 j-cafe/16788679/2026-05-16T16
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Bloomington
END:VEVENT
