ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/O330VgnfgkWT3M9XENdZeA.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Come see our local Red-eared Slider hunt for fish. This progra
 m is held at the Canyon Inn.  \n\nNature Center is open every day from 10 
 am-5 pm EDT in April-Novemember \n\nUpcoming programs can be seen by visit
 ing on.in.gov/mccormickscreek\n\nOur interpretive programs are designed to
  entertain and enrich folks of all ages. Children under 12 must have an ad
 ult with them at the programs.\n\nRegistration is not required for program
 s \\(unless stated\\). All our programs are free \\(unless otherwise noted
 \\). They are open to the public after paying the park entrance fee \\($7 
 in-state & $12 out-of-state\\).\n\nAll our Interpretive programs are liste
 d in Eastern Daylight Savings Time.\n\n\\*Note that during peak visitation
  times\, entry into our park might be delayed. The drive to the Nature Cen
 ter can take 8 minutes. Please plan accordingly. \\*\n\nIf you need more i
 nformation\, call 812-829-2235 ext. 2
LOCATION:McCormick's Creek State Park
URL:https://events.in.gov/event/turtle-feeding-mccormicks-creek-state-park
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Bloomington
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Whose Live Anyway?
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260518T193000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260518T210000
UID:251116wyyLiYILAEmMwwLl5IoCLQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/XOQ-UF9Bs06nWXX4vPOmMg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:WHOSE LIVE ANYWAY?\n\nThe current cast members of the Emmy-nom
 inated TV show Whose Line Is It Anyway? are proud to present their new i
 mprov tour: WHOSE LIVE ANYWAY?\n\nWHOSE LIVE ANYWAY? is 90 minutes of hila
 rious improvised comedy and song all based on audience suggestions. Cast m
 embers Ryan Stiles\, Greg Proops\, Jeff B. Davis\, and Joel Murray will le
 ave you gasping with the very witty scenes they invent before your eyes. A
 udience participation is key to the show so bring your suggestions and you
  might be asked to join the cast onstage! WHOSE LIVE ANYWAY? showcases som
 e of the improv games made famous on the long-running TV show as well as s
 ome exciting new ones\, featuring musical direction by Laura Hall.\n\nAll 
 ages are welcomed\, but please note that some “PG-13” language will be
  used during the performance.
LOCATION:Buskirk Chumley Theater
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#/details/whose-live-anyway/17430981/20
 26-05-18T19
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Bloomington
END:VEVENT
